First a Spark    /IT(For Candlelighting)/XX/PR
/PR
First a spark/PR
then candle glow./PR
/PR
I watched you at sunset time/PR
eyes sparkling in Shabbat light./PR
/PR
Circling above the flames,/PR
my hands pulled/PR
the warmth of Shabbat peace inside./PR
/PR
Praying for a good week and for blessing./PR
/PR
Take time--the lights beckon/PR
for dreams and wonder,/PR
for the candles grow smaller,/PR
the children taller,/PR
even as we pray./PR
/PR
Hold this sunset moment and let it go/PR
into morning light./PR
/PR
Another generationÚs candlesticks/PR
receive the next generationÚs lights./PR
/PR
And somewhere in the middle/PR
we stand, holding hands/PR
with yesterday and tomorrow/PR
linking echoes of ancient melodies/PR
with the breath of our children./PR
/PR
Finding God and hope in their embrace,/PR
renewing days of creation./PR
/PR
In ordinary time--remember--/PR
First a spark/PR
and then candle glow./PR
Sandy Eisenberg Sasso/XX/PR
/PR
