/KAA Prayer / Tefilah/XX/PR
What shall I ask You for, God?/PR
I have everything./PR
ThereÚs nothing I lack./PR
I ask only for one thing/PR
And not for myself alone;/PI/PR
/PR
/PR
/PR
/PL803/XX/PR
ItÚs for many mothers, and children, and fathers--/PR
Not just in this land, but in many lands hostile to each other./PR
IÚd like to ask for Peace./PR
Yes, itÚs Peace I want,/PR
And You, You wonÚt deny the single wish of a child./PR
You created the Land of Peace,/PR
Where stands the City of Peace,/PR
Where stood the Temple of Peace,/PR
But where still there is no Peace.../PR
/PR
What shall I ask You for, God? I have everything./PR
Peace is what I ask for,/PR
Only Peace./PR
Shlomit Grossberg, Age 13, Jerusalem (translated by Dov Vardi)/XX/PR
/PR
When will peace take over?/PR
When will it come, the day?/PR
When with armies and bombs will they do away,/PR
When all this hostility cease,/PR
A day on which battleships/PR
Will become palaces of leisure and fun/PR
Floating on the seas./PR
/PR
A day on which the steel of guns/PR
Will be melted into pleasure cars,/PR
A day on which generals will begin to raise flowers./PR
When peace/PR
Will include all the peoples of these neighboring lands,/PR
When Ishmael and Israel/PR
Will go hand in hand,/PR
And when every Jew/PR
The ArabÚs brother will be./PR
When will it come, the day?/PR
Mahmud Abu Radj, Age 12, Kfar Sachnin (Arab Village)/XX/PR
