The impulse to evil is like one who runs about the world with
a tightly closed hand. Nobody knows what is inside of it.
Everyone asks: "What do you have in your hand?" And they all
think that just what they want most of all is hidden there. And
everyone runs after the impulse to evil. Then the hand is
opened, and it is empty./PR
