When R. Yoh/±anan ben Zakai was on his death bed, his disciples
came to visit him. Before leaving they said, "Master, give us a
farewell blessing." He said to them, "IÚll pray that fearing God
may be as important to you as fearing people." His disciples
asked, "But should we not fear God more than people?" He
replied, "If only you can attain this! When you think of
committing a transgression, you say: `I hope no one sees me!Ú If
the fear of God is no more than this, it will be enough to keep
you from many sins."/PR
Talmud Berah/±ot 28b/XX/PR
