/PL807/XXREADINGS: SHABBAT SHUVAH/XX/PR
/KASHABBAT SHUVAH/PR
Freedom Is A Habit/XX/PR
Freedom is a habit/PR
and a coat worn/PR
some born to wear it/PR
some never to know it./PR
Freedom is cheap/PR
or again as a garment/PR
is so costly/PR
[some] pay their lives/PR
rather than not have it./PR
Freedom is baffling:/PR
[some] having it often/PR
know not they have it/PR
till it is gone and/PR
they no longer have it./PR
What does this mean?/PR
Is it a riddle?/PR
Yes, it is first of all/PR
in the primers of riddles./PR
To be free is so-so:/PR
you can and you canÚt:/PR
walkers can have freedom/PR
only by never walking/PR
away from their freedom:/PR
runners too have freedom/PR
unless they overrun:/PR
eaters have often outeaten/PR
their freedom to eat/PR
and drinkers overdrank/PR
their fine drinking freedom./PR
Carl Sandburg/XX/PR
