/PGREADINGS: TU BISHVAT/XX810/XX/PR
/KATU BISHVAT/XX/PR
On Tu Bishvat/PR
When spring comes,/PR
An angel descends, ledger in hand,/PR
And records each bud, each twig, each tree,/PR
And all our garden flowers./PR
From town to town, from village to village,/PR
The angel makes a winged way,/PR
Searching the valleys, inspecting the hills,/PR
Flying over the desert/PR
And returns to heaven./PR
And when the ledger will be full/PR
Of trees and blossoms and shrubs,/PR
When the desert is turned into a meadow/PR
And all our land is a watered garden,/PR
Messianic days will be with us./PR
Attributed to Shin Shalom (translator unknown)/XX/PR
